1. Deploy a pod named nginx-pod using the nginx:alpine image.
Use imperative commands only.
A: kubectl run nginx-pod --image=nginx:alpine

2. Deploy a redis pod using the redis:alpine image with the labels tier=db.
You can use imperative commands either to create the pod with the labels or to generate a pod definition file, add the labels, and then create the pod from that file.
A: 
kubectl run redis --image=redis:alpine --dry-run=client -oyaml > redis-pod.yaml    //generate a file
Add given labels tier=db under the metadata section.
kubectl create -f redis-pod.yaml    //create the pod from the yaml file
OR
kubectl run redis -l tier=db --image=redis:alpine    //-l means label

3. Create a service named redis-service to expose the existing redis pod within the cluster on port 6379.
Use imperative commands.
A:
kubectl expose pod redis --port=6379 --name=redis-service --type=ClusterIP











